race.comment: SHAULA (4) found more like her best winning an Ascot CL1 and then raced forward again, beaten 2L at Belmont. That's good form, and she maps for the run of the race. A decent chance to bounce. POINT ROCKS (1) improved last time out to score by 1.5L over 1705m at this track. He was only beaten 2L at Ascot prior and if he went back-to-back, it wouldn't surprise. WORCESTER (2) is a better chance than the form line suggests. He's been plainer his last two but raced favourite her last time from the 12 gate. Draws the outside barrier, but can make the finish if he puts his best foot forward. MONTY ZOOMER (7) led and won at Kalgoorlie and then wasn't too far away at Ascot. In the mix.
